The easiest job in the world
is having a baby,

227
00:11:05.937 --> 00:11:07.520 line:80%
and even that takes nine months.

228
00:11:07.812 --> 00:11:12.187 line:80%
I've read on WhatsApp about men
getting pregnant in just two months.

229
00:11:12.270 --> 00:11:15.354 line:80%
Kids are being born in labs now,
without even needing parents.

230
00:11:15.520 --> 00:11:18.062 line:80%
Kids are being made
in test tubes these days.

231
00:11:18.145 --> 00:11:19.437 line:80%
- You get my point?
- Test tubes?

232
00:11:19.520 --> 00:11:20.687 line:80%
- How does that even work?
- Shut up, all of you!

233
00:11:22.229 --> 00:11:23.229 line:80%
Enough with all this random talk!

234
00:11:23.979 --> 00:11:25.854 line:80%
Talking about babies for no reason!
I know how to make a baby.

235
00:11:26.979 --> 00:11:28.395 line:80%
We need to focus on my job.

236
00:11:28.562 --> 00:11:30.270 line:80%
That's exactly what we're talking about.

237
00:11:30.354 --> 00:11:32.812 line:80%
Sister-in-law should've asked
for a couple of years.

238
00:11:33.145 --> 00:11:34.937 line:80%
How is this possible
in just two months, Brother?

239
00:11:35.020 --> 00:11:37.895 line:80%
We're not here to turn my problem
into random sentences.

240
00:11:38.895 --> 00:11:41.062 line:80%
Let's focus on how
I'm going to get a job.

241
00:11:41.520 --> 00:11:43.395 line:80%
You can't even land
a private job in two months,

242
00:11:44.020 --> 00:11:46.229 line:80%
- how will you get a government one?
- Right.

243
00:11:47.187 --> 00:11:49.770 line:80%
Uncle, no one would give you
a job even in two lifetimes.

244
00:11:49.937 --> 00:11:50.979 line:80%
So you'd better not comment on this.

245
00:11:53.104 --> 00:11:55.312 line:80%
A government job is like an eagle's pee -

246
00:11:55.812 --> 00:11:56.895 line:80%
both are rare.

247
00:11:56.979 --> 00:12:00.562 line:80%
Forget about eagle pee,
just tell me where the cloves are?

248
00:12:01.145 --> 00:12:04.395 line:80%
Dad, my butt's on the line,
and you're asking about cloves?

249
00:12:04.604 --> 00:12:08.104 line:80%
I need cloves to spice up the dinner,
not your butt.

250
00:12:09.604 --> 00:12:12.104 line:80%
Keri, kiddo!

251
00:12:12.687 --> 00:12:15.354 line:80%
Grab me some cloves from downstairs!

252
00:12:15.979 --> 00:12:19.062 line:80%
I can't see the tattoo clearly,
pull it down a little.

253
00:12:19.145 --> 00:12:20.229 line:80%
Keri!

254
00:12:20.312 --> 00:12:22.020 line:80%
Don't you all have any shame?

255
00:12:22.062 --> 00:12:24.145 line:80%
You just got back
from the police station yesterday.

256
00:12:24.229 --> 00:12:27.104 line:80%
Now everyone in the society
is going to think the Tiwaris

257
00:12:27.187 --> 00:12:28.729 line:80%
are shamelessly celebrating.

258
00:12:29.020 --> 00:12:32.812 line:80%
It's Sunday today, society's on holiday.

259
00:12:32.979 --> 00:12:34.395 line:80%
Pull it down a bit.

260
00:12:35.729 --> 00:12:38.145 line:80%
I'm trying to show you my tattoo,
and you're just

261
00:12:38.229 --> 00:12:40.145 line:80%
- showing me your level instead.
- Did you get stuck in there?

262
00:12:42.979 --> 00:12:43.979 line:80%
- What?
- What?

263
00:12:44.354 --> 00:12:45.895 line:80%
You don't even let me take
a dump in peace.

264
00:12:45.979 --> 00:12:47.020 line:80%
Get out of my way.

265
00:12:47.812 --> 00:12:48.979 line:80%
It doesn't even look like you took a dump.

266
00:12:50.145 --> 00:12:51.937 line:80%
Fine,
I'll leave it there tomorrow for you

267
00:12:52.020 --> 00:12:53.020 line:80%
- to see as proof.
- Whatever.

268
00:12:53.062 --> 00:12:54.187 line:80%
Kiddo!

269
00:12:54.687 --> 00:12:57.062 line:80%
Go grab me some cloves from downstairs!

270
00:12:57.145 --> 00:12:58.354 line:80%
Coming!

271
00:12:59.770 --> 00:13:01.312 line:80%
You've got so many people here,

272
00:13:01.395 --> 00:13:02.770 line:80%
why didn't you just ask one
of them to get it?

273
00:13:02.854 --> 00:13:05.020 line:80%
We're having an important meeting, kiddo.

274
00:13:06.979 --> 00:13:08.145 line:80%
What's this meeting about?

275
00:13:09.562 --> 00:13:12.312 line:80%
Your sister-in-law's dad
has set a condition-

276
00:13:12.395 --> 00:13:16.020 line:80%
if your brother doesn't land
a government job within two months,

277
00:13:16.145 --> 00:13:17.604 line:80%
your sister-in-law stays as she is,

278
00:13:17.687 --> 00:13:19.062 line:80%
but your "brother" will have to change.

279
00:13:19.729 --> 00:13:20.729 line:80%
I see.

280
00:13:20.812 --> 00:13:23.562 line:80%
He's not going to get a government job
just sitting at home.

281
00:13:24.145 --> 00:13:25.479 line:80%
Nobody asked for your advice

282
00:13:25.729 --> 00:13:26.645 line:80%
Mind your own business.

283
00:13:26.729 --> 00:13:27.937 line:80%
I'm not giving you any.

284
00:13:28.020 --> 00:13:29.145 line:80%
I don't want it. Buzz off.

285
00:13:30.812 --> 00:13:33.812 line:80%
By the way, I know someone
who might be able to help.

286
00:13:33.979 --> 00:13:35.770 line:80%
But I guess you
don't want my help, right?

287
00:13:35.854 --> 00:13:36.770 line:80%
Fine.

288
00:13:37.145 --> 00:13:38.812 line:80%
Hey Keri, Keri, Keri!

289
00:13:40.145 --> 00:13:43.104 line:80%
My sister is so sweet!

290
00:13:43.187 --> 00:13:44.895 line:80%
Come here, come here, sit with me.

291
00:13:45.020 --> 00:13:47.020 line:80%
You can even sleep in front
of the cooler if you want.

292
00:13:47.395 --> 00:13:49.020 line:80%
Dad, did you make any
kheer
(sweets) for Keri?

293
00:13:49.104 --> 00:13:51.062 line:80%
Yes, I made some.

294
00:13:51.979 --> 00:13:53.145 line:80%
Do you know someone who can help?

295
00:13:53.687 --> 00:13:54.854 line:80%
I'll take you to him tomorrow.

296
00:14:09.979 --> 00:14:11.729 line:80%
I think he stores them here.

297
00:14:11.812 --> 00:14:12.979 line:80%
Just like a monkey.

298
00:14:13.020 --> 00:14:14.020 line:80%
Hmm.

299
00:14:14.812 --> 00:14:16.645 line:80%
Should I order 100-150 more
Kachoris
(snacks) for you?

300
00:14:17.020 --> 00:14:18.187 line:80%
How about some
Jalebis
(sweets)
instead, Brother?

301
00:14:18.270 --> 00:14:19.812 line:80%
Will you keep eating
or actually say something?

302
00:14:21.395 --> 00:14:23.145 line:80%
How is this possible in just two months?

303
00:14:24.187 --> 00:14:25.604 line:80%
I told you,

304
00:14:25.770 --> 00:14:27.812 line:80%
even the easiest job
in the world takes nine months.

305
00:14:28.312 --> 00:14:30.229 line:80%
I wasted so much time because of you!

306
00:14:30.562 --> 00:14:32.770 line:80%
Listen, you're going to pay
for all the
Kachoris
.

307
00:14:32.854 --> 00:14:33.562 line:80%
Hey, make sure he pays for everything!

308
00:14:33.687 --> 00:14:34.895 line:80%
Where are you going? Stop.

309
00:14:34.979 --> 00:14:36.145 line:80%
I'm so going to whack you.

310
00:14:36.437 --> 00:14:38.229 line:80%
I've already wasted
so much time because of you.

311
00:14:38.312 --> 00:14:39.979 line:80%
Out of the two months I have,
I've already lost two days.

312
00:14:40.020 --> 00:14:42.062 line:80%
You spent them drinking beer!

313
00:14:42.145 --> 00:14:43.020 line:80%
Who do you think you are?

314
00:14:43.062 --> 00:14:44.562 line:80%
You can't do anything by yourself.

315
00:14:44.770 --> 00:14:46.979 line:80%
I got your Aadhar card made.
I got you your passport.

316
00:14:47.020 --> 00:14:48.729 line:80%
- And I'm the one who convinced Titli to...
- Hey,

317
00:14:48.812 --> 00:14:49.979 line:80%
don't bring Titli into this!
I'm warning you.

318
00:14:50.020 --> 00:14:51.020 line:80%
Titli won't be able to do anything either,

319
00:14:51.062 --> 00:14:52.229 line:80%
her father will just send her away.

320
00:14:52.312 --> 00:14:53.020 line:80%
- Got it?
- Keri, I swear,

321
00:14:53.104 --> 00:14:55.104 line:80%
I'll stuff you inside a
samosa
wrapper
and fry you up!

322
00:14:55.187 --> 00:14:56.312 line:80%
Go ahead! I dare you to do it right now!

323
00:14:56.395 --> 00:14:57.895 line:80%
Why should I? I'm not the cook here!

324
00:14:57.979 --> 00:14:59.895 line:80%
- And the whole of Banaras knows...
- Calm down, both of you!

325
00:15:00.020 --> 00:15:01.562 line:80%
- Stop fighting.
- Yes.

326
00:15:02.020 --> 00:15:03.645 line:80%
He's trying to say something.
Let's hear him out.

327
00:15:04.562 --> 00:15:05.729 line:80%
There's one option.

328
00:15:06.729 --> 00:15:07.437 line:80%
What?

329
00:15:07.520 --> 00:15:08.270 line:80%
Bhagwan
. (God)

330
00:15:08.562 --> 00:15:09.645 line:80%
- Damn it.
- Huh?

331
00:15:09.895 --> 00:15:10.937 line:80%
Bhagwan!

332
00:15:11.020 --> 00:15:13.062 line:80%
Great choice!
Come here, you...

333
00:15:13.395 --> 00:15:16.062 line:80%
We've already handed over
his fate in God's hands.

334
00:15:16.145 --> 00:15:18.020 line:80%
No, I'm not talking about God,

335
00:15:18.354 --> 00:15:19.854 line:80%
I'm talking about Bhagwan Das.

336
00:15:20.020 --> 00:15:21.687 line:80%
Who's this Bhagwan Das?

337
00:15:22.645 --> 00:15:24.062 line:80%
I'll take you to him.

338
00:15:25.520 --> 00:15:26.979 line:80%
Here it is. Stop, stop, stop!

339
00:15:28.437 --> 00:15:29.687 line:80%
We've arrived! We're here!

340
00:15:29.770 --> 00:15:30.812 line:80%
Let's go. Take this.

341
00:15:31.020 --> 00:15:31.645 line:80%
Alright?

342
00:15:31.729 --> 00:15:32.645 line:80%
Yeah? Go.

343
00:15:33.270 --> 00:15:34.479 line:80%
This one.

344
00:15:34.645 --> 00:15:36.354 line:80%
It's an amazing place.
Let's go, sir.

345
00:15:36.437 --> 00:15:38.020 line:80%
- Come on, Your Highness.
- What is this place?

346
00:15:38.062 --> 00:15:40.354 line:80%
Just follow me.
It's a one-stop shop for all your needs.

347
00:15:40.645 --> 00:15:41.770 line:80%
Follow me.

348
00:15:43.645 --> 00:15:44.979 line:80%
We're here.

349
00:15:47.687 --> 00:15:48.979 line:80%
Greetings, Guruji.

350
00:15:49.395 --> 00:15:51.104 line:80%
- Greetings, Guruji.
- Bless you.

351
00:15:51.270 --> 00:15:52.895 line:80%
I don't know Kathak,

352
00:15:52.979 --> 00:15:55.937 line:80%
but if there's a government job
in breakdancing,

353
00:15:56.020 --> 00:15:57.854 line:80%
- I'm your guy.
- He's not our guy, Bhagwan is upstairs.

354
00:15:57.937 --> 00:15:59.187 line:80%
- Let's go.
- Come on, man...

355
00:15:59.270 --> 00:16:00.437 line:80%
It's okay, you can go ahead.

356
00:16:00.520 --> 00:16:01.395 line:80%
Kathak Guruji!

357
00:16:01.479 --> 00:16:03.187 line:80%
- Indian culture!
- It's alright.

358
00:16:03.979 --> 00:16:07.020 line:80%
I also wanted to learn,
but my waist doesn't agree.

359
00:16:13.645 --> 00:16:14.812 line:80%
Damn it, it's dead.

360
00:16:15.395 --> 00:16:16.395 line:80%
Who's dead?

361
00:16:16.937 --> 00:16:18.437 line:80%
The snake.

362
00:16:18.979 --> 00:16:20.562 line:80%
What am I supposed to do now?

363
00:16:21.145 --> 00:16:22.270 line:80%
Look Brother,

364
00:16:23.687 --> 00:16:25.604 line:80%
the list of the final 15 candidates

365
00:16:25.687 --> 00:16:28.937 line:80%
for the irrigation department
is right here.

366
00:16:31.104 --> 00:16:34.062 line:80%
And about the other forms you filled...

367
00:16:35.312 --> 00:16:37.520 line:80%
None of their results
are coming out this year.

368
00:16:38.145 --> 00:16:40.895 line:80%
- Oh no!
- Guruji, he won't be able to get married.

369
00:16:41.354 --> 00:16:42.645 line:80%
His love life is at stake here, you see.

370
00:16:42.729 --> 00:16:45.020 line:80%
Why do you bring matters
involving love to me?

371
00:16:45.062 --> 00:16:46.770 line:80%
Can't you see I'm busy here?

372
00:16:46.854 --> 00:16:48.854 line:80%
I'll have to make some effort
for this, Brother.

373
00:16:48.937 --> 00:16:50.979 line:80%
Please, Guruji, help me out here.

374
00:16:51.395 --> 00:16:53.687 line:80%
I really love her a lot.
You can ask anyone, they'll tell you.

375
00:16:53.770 --> 00:16:54.937 line:80%
- Go ahead, tell him.
- Yeah, they're seriously in love.

376
00:16:55.020 --> 00:16:56.979 line:80%
- Just like Laila and Majnu.
- They're crazy about each other.

377
00:16:57.270 --> 00:17:00.645 line:80%
Brother, he actually landed
a government job!

378
00:17:00.729 --> 00:17:01.937 line:80%
Thank you, Guruji!

379
00:17:02.020 --> 00:17:03.020 line:80%
Everyone, say it together:

380
00:17:03.104 --> 00:17:04.729 line:80%
Har Har Mahadev!
(Everyone is an embodiment of Lord Shiva)

381
00:17:04.812 --> 00:17:07.062 line:80%
- Har Har Mahadev!- Har Har Mahadev!

382
00:17:07.229 --> 00:17:08.687 line:80%
Guruji, can I tell you something?

383
00:17:08.770 --> 00:17:10.354 line:80%
Not just in name, Guruji,

384
00:17:10.479 --> 00:17:12.395 line:80%
- you're actually like god to me.
- He's right, Guruji.

385
00:17:12.562 --> 00:17:13.979 line:80%
That's fine.

386
00:17:14.854 --> 00:17:16.687 line:80%
Rs. 600,000 upfront before you join.

387
00:17:17.104 --> 00:17:19.020 line:80%
Wait, I get Rs. 600,000 before joining?

388
00:17:19.062 --> 00:17:20.062 line:80%
Guruji!

389
00:17:20.145 --> 00:17:23.729 line:80%
- Guruji, you're not just a god, you're...
- Silly...

390
00:17:24.104 --> 00:17:26.104 line:80%
You won't get it, you have to pay up.

391
00:17:26.979 --> 00:17:28.229 line:80%
- I have to pay?
- Yes, you do.

392
00:17:28.312 --> 00:17:29.687 line:80%
A Rs. 200,000 advance.

393
00:17:30.229 --> 00:17:32.645 line:80%
Rs. 200,000 in advance?

394
00:17:32.729 --> 00:17:33.395 line:80%
Yes.

395
00:17:33.479 --> 00:17:35.020 line:80%
I'm giving you this price
since you came with him.

396
00:17:35.062 --> 00:17:36.104 line:80%
He's practically family.

397
00:17:36.187 --> 00:17:38.145 line:80%
Right, Pramod?
Wait, your name's Pramod, right?

398
00:17:38.229 --> 00:17:40.437 line:80%
No, my name's Sushil.

399
00:17:41.020 --> 00:17:43.395 line:80%
Anyway, I quoted that price
since he's practically family.

400
00:17:43.562 --> 00:17:46.937 line:80%
Otherwise, I never charge less than
Rs. 1 million, no matter what.

401
00:17:47.020 --> 00:17:48.145 line:80%
Yeah, he's right.

402
00:17:48.437 --> 00:17:49.687 line:80%
So...?

403
00:17:50.354 --> 00:17:51.687 line:80%
Guys...

404
00:17:53.020 --> 00:17:54.812 line:80%
Okay... Rs. 200,000 it is.

405
00:17:54.895 --> 00:17:55.937 line:80%
How are we okay with Rs. 200,000?

406
00:17:56.020 --> 00:17:57.312 line:80%
How are you going
to come up with Rs. 200,000?

407
00:17:57.395 --> 00:17:59.729 line:80%
Guruji, how am I supposed
to pay Rs. 200,000?

408
00:17:59.937 --> 00:18:01.770 line:80%
Don't expect
Bhagwan
(god)
to solve everything,

409
00:18:01.854 --> 00:18:03.645 line:80%
sometimes you've got to do it yourself.

410
00:18:03.729 --> 00:18:05.645 line:80%
Work hard, you're still young.

411
00:18:05.812 --> 00:18:07.020 line:80%
Find a way to get it.

412
00:18:07.229 --> 00:18:10.104 line:80%
Otherwise, you can join
this coaching class for Rs. 600 a month.

413
00:18:10.437 --> 00:18:11.770 line:80%
You'll study here for 4-6 years,

414
00:18:11.854 --> 00:18:14.020 line:80%
then by year 7 or 8,
I can get you a peon's job.

415
00:18:14.270 --> 00:18:15.395 line:80%
A peon?

416
00:18:15.479 --> 00:18:17.229 line:80%
No, Guruji, I don't want to be a peon!

417
00:18:17.479 --> 00:18:18.395 line:80%
You...

418
00:18:18.479 --> 00:18:19.729 line:80%
Why don't you...

419
00:18:20.895 --> 00:18:22.979 line:80%
You stall this irrigation department list.

420
00:18:23.020 --> 00:18:24.604 line:80%
I'll figure out how to get the money.

421
00:18:24.687 --> 00:18:25.395 line:80%
Okay.

422
00:18:25.479 --> 00:18:27.229 line:80%
You can keep the peon job for me.

423
00:18:27.520 --> 00:18:28.979 line:80%
Sure, you look like one anyway.

424
00:18:29.020 --> 00:18:30.020 line:80%
Yeah, yeah.

425
00:18:30.312 --> 00:18:32.270 line:80%
You seriously want to be a peon?

426
00:18:33.479 --> 00:18:35.729 line:80%
I just can't stand being single anymore,
Nephew.

427
00:18:38.270 --> 00:18:39.645 line:80%
Okay, Guruji.

428
00:18:39.729 --> 00:18:42.104 line:80%
Stall this list for me,
I'll figure out the money.

429
00:18:42.562 --> 00:18:44.437 line:80%
- Stall this list for me.
- Yes, Rs. 200,000 in advance.

430
00:18:44.520 --> 00:18:45.770 line:80%
-
Har Har Mahadev!
- Okay, Brother.

431
00:18:45.854 --> 00:18:47.020 line:80%
- Guruji, take care of me too.
- See you, take care.

432
00:18:47.062 --> 00:18:48.354 line:80%
I work for Mr. Gupta.

433
00:18:48.437 --> 00:18:51.520 line:80%
- Yeah, I got it, you work for Mr. Gupta.
-
The butterfly flew, flew, and flew away.

434
00:18:51.687 --> 00:18:55.729 line:80%
You make tall claims, why...

435
00:18:55.812 --> 00:18:59.395 line:80%
Then blush and sigh.

436
00:19:00.895 --> 00:19:02.020 line:80%
Tittu,

437
00:19:03.020 --> 00:19:05.562 line:80%
you're not thinking about running
away anymore, are you?

438
00:19:05.812 --> 00:19:06.770 line:80%
Why do you ask?

439
00:19:06.854 --> 00:19:09.937 line:80%
Just thinking, what will we do
if I don't get a job in two months?

440
00:19:10.437 --> 00:19:12.729 line:80%
You and your negativity!

441
00:19:13.395 --> 00:19:15.104 line:80%
What's the problem
with getting a job now?

442
00:19:15.187 --> 00:19:16.687 line:80%
Bhagwan's helping you with that, right?

443
00:19:16.854 --> 00:19:20.062 line:80%
Yeah, but he wants Rs. 600,000
before I join,

444
00:19:20.270 --> 00:19:22.270 line:80%
and Rs. 200,000 advance.

445
00:19:22.437 --> 00:19:24.854 line:80%
I'll get you that as dowry.

446
00:19:25.312 --> 00:19:27.062 line:80%
My dad won't send me off empty-handed.

447
00:19:27.145 --> 00:19:29.937 line:80%
