01:09:23.729 --> 01:09:24.562 line:80%
Hey!

1582
01:09:24.812 --> 01:09:25.812 line:80%
- Move.
- What's going on here?

1583
01:09:25.895 --> 01:09:26.479 line:80%
Brother!

1584
01:09:26.562 --> 01:09:28.354 line:80%
I came to drop these mattresses,
and she stopped me.

1585
01:09:28.520 --> 01:09:29.812 line:80%
- Shut up.
- She did, yeah.

1586
01:09:29.895 --> 01:09:33.937 line:80%
My life's a mess,
and you two are over here romancing?

1587
01:09:34.020 --> 01:09:36.229 line:80%
Come on, Brother, just hear me out.
Keri, explain it to him.

1588
01:09:36.312 --> 01:09:37.770 line:80%
What are you doing? Let go of his neck.

1589
01:09:37.854 --> 01:09:38.937 line:80%
I should let go of his neck?

1590
01:09:39.020 --> 01:09:40.270 line:80%
Fine, I'll let it go.

1591
01:09:40.562 --> 01:09:42.854 line:80%
I'll hit him with my shoes instead!

1592
01:09:42.937 --> 01:09:45.354 line:80%
- Bro, Brother, I got you that job!
- Quit it.

1593
01:09:45.437 --> 01:09:46.312 line:80%
So, should I just marry

1594
01:09:46.395 --> 01:09:47.479 line:80%
- my sister to you now?
- No!

1595
01:09:47.562 --> 01:09:48.437 line:80%
What are you doing?

1596
01:09:48.520 --> 01:09:50.270 line:80%
He's your future brother-in-law.

1597
01:09:50.354 --> 01:09:51.562 line:80%
Yeah, your brother-in-law.

1598
01:09:51.645 --> 01:09:52.854 line:80%
This baby beaver?

1599
01:09:53.229 --> 01:09:54.895 line:80%
Couldn't you find anyone
better than this cricket?

1600
01:09:54.979 --> 01:09:56.895 line:80%
Brother, we really love each other.

1601
01:09:56.979 --> 01:09:58.895 line:80%
- We're totally crazy about each other.
- True love, man, true love!

1602
01:09:58.979 --> 01:10:01.020 line:80%
Hold on, let me get rid of all this love.

1603
01:10:01.520 --> 01:10:04.187 line:80%
Do one thing: just jump off the roof. Go.

1604
01:10:04.270 --> 01:10:05.562 line:80%
Have you lost your mind?

1605
01:10:05.645 --> 01:10:07.104 line:80%
- Just jump.
- It's too high.

1606
01:10:07.187 --> 01:10:08.979 line:80%
- Stay there, Brother, or I'll jump.
- Keri, get out of my way.

1607
01:10:09.062 --> 01:10:10.604 line:80%
Have you lost your mind?
He'll jump! What are you doing?

1608
01:10:10.687 --> 01:10:12.145 line:80%
I'll end up hurting you,
Keri, get out of my way.

1609
01:10:12.229 --> 01:10:14.854 line:80%
Har Har Mahadev!

1610
01:10:18.187 --> 01:10:20.145 line:80%
Who does that, man?!

1611
01:10:21.770 --> 01:10:25.562 line:80%
Does this family's only son-in-law
have any respect at all?

1612
01:10:29.979 --> 01:10:31.145 line:80%
He's alive.

1613
01:10:32.562 --> 01:10:33.687 line:80%
For now.

1614
01:10:37.395 --> 01:10:38.812 line:80%
What's up, Mr. Groom?

1615
01:10:39.020 --> 01:10:40.229 line:80%
Where are you off to, huh?

1616
01:10:42.062 --> 01:10:44.062 line:80%
Why should I tell you
where am I going every day, huh?

1617
01:10:44.395 --> 01:10:45.604 line:80%
Are you my dad or what?

1618
01:10:47.187 --> 01:10:48.062 line:80%
Mind your own business!

1619
01:10:49.312 --> 01:10:50.187 line:80%
Ugh!

1620
01:11:01.062 --> 01:11:03.604 line:80%
So, you're telling me
you're stuck on the 29th

1621
01:11:03.687 --> 01:11:05.145 line:80%
because you didn't keep your pledge?

1622
01:11:05.354 --> 01:11:07.145 line:80%
I say that every day!

1623
01:11:07.645 --> 01:11:08.187 line:80%
Okay.

1624
01:11:08.312 --> 01:11:09.270 line:80%
I say that every day!

1625
01:11:11.229 --> 01:11:12.729 line:80%
- Sister-in-law! I seek you blessings.
- Yeah, yeah, okay.

1626
01:11:12.812 --> 01:11:13.687 line:80%
What happened?

1627
01:11:13.812 --> 01:11:15.020 line:80%
I don't know, Titli.

1628
01:11:15.104 --> 01:11:16.395 line:80%
It's all flying over my head right now.

1629
01:11:16.479 --> 01:11:17.895 line:80%
He says he's stuck on the 29th.

1630
01:11:18.020 --> 01:11:18.812 line:80%
Huh?

1631
01:11:19.729 --> 01:11:21.062 line:80%
What happened, Babu?

1632
01:11:21.437 --> 01:11:25.062 line:80%
Keri called me and said you caused
a scene at home and just stormed out.

1633
01:11:25.145 --> 01:11:26.104 line:80%
What happened?

1634
01:11:26.229 --> 01:11:27.354 line:80%
Nothing happened.

1635
01:11:28.270 --> 01:11:30.187 line:80%
You go, I'll handle it. Just leave.

1636
01:11:32.354 --> 01:11:33.604 line:80%
I left my henna ceremony...

1637
01:11:33.687 --> 01:11:34.854 line:80%
I left my henna ceremony in the middle,

1638
01:11:34.937 --> 01:11:36.479 line:80%
I've been walking around
Banaras dressed as a bride.

1639
01:11:36.562 --> 01:11:37.229 line:80%
I can never seem to handle things
by myself.

1640
01:11:37.312 --> 01:11:38.229 line:80%
You're the one
who's been taking care of everything.

1641
01:11:38.312 --> 01:11:39.229 line:80%
I just keep messing everything up.

1642
01:11:39.312 --> 01:11:40.812 line:80%
You still haven't paid for the lehenga.

1643
01:11:40.895 --> 01:11:42.270 line:80%
I know everything, okay?!

1644
01:11:42.520 --> 01:11:43.437 line:80%
Wow,

1645
01:11:43.895 --> 01:11:44.854 line:80%
that's amazing!

1646
01:11:48.437 --> 01:11:49.395 line:80%
Why...

1647
01:11:49.979 --> 01:11:51.854 line:80%
why can't you just understand
what I'm trying to say for once?

1648
01:11:52.979 --> 01:11:53.979 line:80%
I'm...

1649
01:11:54.812 --> 01:11:56.229 line:80%
Why do I even bother trying? Forget it.

1650
01:11:56.479 --> 01:11:57.229 line:80%
Babu...

1651
01:11:57.312 --> 01:11:58.937 line:80%
I'M NOT BABU!

1652
01:11:59.687 --> 01:12:00.770 line:80%
My name's Ranjan.

1653
01:12:02.020 --> 01:12:03.062 line:80%
See what I mean?

1654
01:12:13.562 --> 01:12:14.895 line:80%
- Hey...
- Priest!

1655
01:12:14.979 --> 01:12:16.437 line:80%
- Priest! Priest! Priest!
- Who is it?

1656
01:12:16.520 --> 01:12:17.479 line:80%
Greetings.

1657
01:12:18.312 --> 01:12:19.187 line:80%
Mahadev!

1658
01:12:20.062 --> 01:12:22.895 line:80%
Remember me? I gave you Rs. 100
in cash and Re. 1 through UPI?

1659
01:12:23.604 --> 01:12:25.062 line:80%
- Yeah, yeah, I remember.
- Right.

1660
01:12:25.687 --> 01:12:28.395 line:80%
So, what's going on?
In the middle of the night...

1661
01:12:28.479 --> 01:12:31.937 line:80%
I'm in big trouble.

1662
01:12:33.145 --> 01:12:34.062 line:80%
Big trouble?

1663
01:12:34.145 --> 01:12:35.020 line:80%
Yeah.

1664
01:12:35.187 --> 01:12:36.145 line:80%
What happened?

1665
01:12:36.812 --> 01:12:38.062 line:80%
I can't keep my pledge.

1666
01:12:39.145 --> 01:12:40.145 line:80%
What pledge?

1667
01:12:40.395 --> 01:12:41.437 line:80%
The one about doing a good deed.

1668
01:12:41.729 --> 01:12:42.895 line:80%
What good deed?

1669
01:12:44.437 --> 01:12:47.520 line:80%
Priest, you told me to make a pledge
to do a good deed, and I did.

1670
01:12:48.395 --> 01:12:50.395 line:80%
I didn't say which good deed, though.

1671
01:12:50.979 --> 01:12:52.145 line:80%
Now I'm stuck because of it.

1672
01:12:52.479 --> 01:12:55.645 line:80%
I've fed cows, dogs, monkeys,
and humans-everyone.

1673
01:12:55.895 --> 01:12:57.854 line:80%
I've donated a lot of money too.

1674
01:12:57.979 --> 01:13:02.895 line:80%
I've even lit a lamp under every kind
of tree-big, small, thin, thick.

1675
01:13:03.312 --> 01:13:04.895 line:80%
But somehow,
I just can't fulfill my pledge.

1676
01:13:05.479 --> 01:13:06.312 line:80%
You get what I mean?

1677
01:13:06.437 --> 01:13:07.395 line:80%
Hmm.

1678
01:13:07.854 --> 01:13:08.770 line:80%
Priest, please...

1679
01:13:09.104 --> 01:13:10.395 line:80%
please help me out.

1680
01:13:12.437 --> 01:13:13.729 line:80%
You have to do something.

1681
01:13:14.312 --> 01:13:15.479 line:80%
Yes, I will.

1682
01:13:16.270 --> 01:13:17.520 line:80%
Then do it.

1683
01:13:19.395 --> 01:13:20.812 line:80%
I see, I see, I see.

1684
01:13:20.895 --> 01:13:22.312 line:80%
Sorry, sorry.

1685
01:13:22.895 --> 01:13:26.562 line:80%
Here, Rs. 100.
I'll send Re. 1 through UPI.

1686
01:13:26.645 --> 01:13:29.395 line:80%
No, son, this is a big problem.

1687
01:13:29.770 --> 01:13:30.562 line:80%
It is.

1688
01:13:31.062 --> 01:13:33.187 line:80%
So my fee will be Rs. 501.

1689
01:13:38.895 --> 01:13:40.604 line:80%
Now, quickly, tell me the solution.

1690
01:13:41.812 --> 01:13:43.062 line:80%
Son, the thing is,

1691
01:13:44.187 --> 01:13:49.479 line:80%
all the good deeds
you just mentioned are fine.

1692
01:13:49.562 --> 01:13:50.520 line:80%
Yes.

1693
01:13:52.312 --> 01:13:57.729 line:80%
But your problem is different.

1694
01:13:59.270 --> 01:14:00.645 line:80%
Is it possible that...

1695
01:14:03.687 --> 01:14:05.479 line:80%
you hurt someone's feelings?

1696
01:14:06.562 --> 01:14:07.937 line:80%
I...

1697
01:14:08.020 --> 01:14:13.145 line:80%
Yes, you've either knowingly
or unknowingly hurt someone's feelings.

1698
01:14:14.270 --> 01:14:19.895 line:80%
That's why your pledge is stuck.

1699
01:14:29.979 --> 01:14:32.604 line:80%
Brother Ranjan, you look awesome!

1700
01:14:32.687 --> 01:14:33.729 line:80%
Good morning!

1701
01:14:33.812 --> 01:14:36.229 line:80%
Good morning!
Now, try this on.

1702
01:14:36.312 --> 01:14:37.229 line:80%
Here you go.

1703
01:14:37.979 --> 01:14:40.562 line:80%
It's a masterpiece.

1704
01:14:40.729 --> 01:14:41.687 line:80%
It's awesome!

1705
01:14:42.937 --> 01:14:44.479 line:80%
You look like a clown.

1706
01:14:44.812 --> 01:14:45.687 line:80%
Huh?

1707
01:14:45.979 --> 01:14:47.312 line:80%
How dare you!

1708
01:14:47.687 --> 01:14:50.354 line:80%
She's talking to me, not you.

1709
01:14:50.729 --> 01:14:52.354 line:80%
Well, then she's right.

1710
01:14:52.729 --> 01:14:54.979 line:80%
- What... what are you doing?
- Bless me.

1711
01:14:55.104 --> 01:14:56.104 line:80%
What's this?

1712
01:14:56.312 --> 01:14:58.062 line:80%
I'm asking for your blessings, Father.

1713
01:14:58.145 --> 01:14:59.479 line:80%
Father? Who's Father?

1714
01:14:59.687 --> 01:15:02.104 line:80%
You're my father, and I'm your son.

1715
01:15:02.479 --> 01:15:03.479 line:80%
Huh?

1716
01:15:04.104 --> 01:15:06.687 line:80%
What have you made?

1717
01:15:06.854 --> 01:15:09.312 line:80%
It looks more like a bag than a sherwani.

1718
01:15:09.395 --> 01:15:11.687 line:80%
Calm down. Father, please calm down.

1719
01:15:12.479 --> 01:15:13.520 line:80%
It's okay.

1720
01:15:13.604 --> 01:15:14.937 line:80%
Please forgive him.

1721
01:15:16.062 --> 01:15:20.229 line:80%
Take it back and fix it.

1722
01:15:20.604 --> 01:15:21.395 line:80%
Huh?

1723
01:15:21.687 --> 01:15:23.687 line:80%
Because I've got plenty of time.

1724
01:15:27.645 --> 01:15:29.145 line:80%
If I've hurt you in any way,

1725
01:15:29.479 --> 01:15:30.729 line:80%
please forgive me.

1726
01:15:36.687 --> 01:15:39.520 line:80%
- So... sorry, Brother.
- No, no, no need.

1727
01:15:39.729 --> 01:15:40.770 line:80%
Are you okay?

1728
01:15:40.854 --> 01:15:41.979 line:80%
Yeah, Brother.

1729
01:15:42.687 --> 01:15:44.562 line:80%
If I've hurt you in any way,

1730
01:15:45.062 --> 01:15:46.437 line:80%
please forgive me.

1731
01:15:46.604 --> 01:15:47.604 line:80%
Huh?

1732
01:15:49.145 --> 01:15:50.770 line:80%
And take good care of my sister.

1733
01:15:51.562 --> 01:15:52.520 line:80%
Okay, Brother.

1734
01:15:52.895 --> 01:15:54.979 line:80%
A lot of people keep going to the terrace,

1735
01:15:55.104 --> 01:15:56.312 line:80%
so be careful.

1736
01:15:58.229 --> 01:16:00.145 line:80%
You should try hanging exercises,
you know.

1737
01:16:01.437 --> 01:16:02.604 line:80%
Okay, Brother.

1738
01:16:03.979 --> 01:16:05.187 line:80%
Hurry up, girls.

1739
01:16:05.270 --> 01:16:07.062 line:80%
Mix some more of this, will you?
We need enough to apply on him.

1740
01:16:07.145 --> 01:16:08.854 line:80%
- Okay, Aunty.
- You're just wasting time talking.

1741
01:16:08.937 --> 01:16:10.812 line:80%
I seek your blessing, Mother.

1742
01:16:10.895 --> 01:16:11.770 line:80%
Such anger?

1743
01:16:11.854 --> 01:16:15.062 line:80%
Wow, where did the sun come from today?

1744
01:16:15.145 --> 01:16:16.395 line:80%
Yes, Brother-in-law?

1745
01:16:16.604 --> 01:16:19.020 line:80%
You're touching your mom's feet today,

1746
01:16:19.187 --> 01:16:21.312 line:80%
but tomorrow you'll be taking
orders from your wife.

1747
01:16:21.395 --> 01:16:22.645 line:80%
Hey!

1748
01:16:22.937 --> 01:16:24.937 line:80%
I'm really looking forward
to that "tomorrow," Sister-in-law.

1749
01:16:25.895 --> 01:16:27.479 line:80%
It just needs to get here.

1750
01:16:29.104 --> 01:16:31.729 line:80%
Mom, I'm done, come clean me up.

1751
01:16:31.895 --> 01:16:33.729 line:80%
Sister-in-law, forget the turmeric

1752
01:16:33.895 --> 01:16:35.979 line:80%
and clean up the mess inside first.

1753
01:16:36.062 --> 01:16:37.062 line:80%
I'm going, I'm going, Brother-in-law.

1754
01:16:37.145 --> 01:16:40.229 line:80%
And if I've hurt you in any way,
please forgive me.

1755
01:16:40.479 --> 01:16:43.062 line:80%
Stop talking, sit down,
and apply some turmeric.

1756
01:16:43.395 --> 01:16:45.270 line:80%
Anything you say, Mother.
Just give me a minute.

1757
01:16:45.520 --> 01:16:46.854 line:80%
Has he lost it?

1758
01:16:46.937 --> 01:16:48.062 line:80%
What's wrong with him?

1759
01:16:48.145 --> 01:16:49.270 line:80%
Forget him.

1760
01:16:54.854 --> 01:16:55.854 line:80%
Sorry, Brother.

1761
01:16:55.979 --> 01:16:58.562 line:80%
- It fell by mistake.
- No, no,

1762
01:16:58.979 --> 01:17:00.354 line:80%
it was meant to fall.

1763
01:17:00.479 --> 01:17:01.895 line:80%
It's part of its destiny.

1764
01:17:02.229 --> 01:17:03.187 line:80%
Are you okay?

1765
01:17:03.437 --> 01:17:04.312 line:80%
Yeah.

1766
01:17:04.937 --> 01:17:07.062 line:80%
You've done such a great job
decorating my house.

1767
01:17:07.437 --> 01:17:08.562 line:80%
Thank you.

1768
01:17:09.062 --> 01:17:10.770 line:80%
And if I've hurt you in any way,

1769
01:17:11.229 --> 01:17:12.354 line:80%
please forgive me.

1770
01:17:12.562 --> 01:17:15.187 line:80%
Hey, magpie, have you lost your mind?

1771
01:17:15.312 --> 01:17:17.020 line:80%
Why are you apologizing to everyone?

1772
01:17:17.104 --> 01:17:18.812 line:80%
So what?
Go apply the turmeric.

1773
01:17:18.895 --> 01:17:19.812 line:80%
Father, please don't be mad.

1774
01:17:19.895 --> 01:17:22.187 line:80%
What are you doing up there?
Get down now!

1775
01:17:22.270 --> 01:17:24.145 line:80%
If I've hurt you in any way,
please forgive me.

1776
01:17:24.229 --> 01:17:25.145 line:80%
Mahadev!

1777
01:17:25.229 --> 01:17:26.395 line:80%
Mahadev! If I've hurt you in any way,
please forgive me.

1778
01:17:26.479 --> 01:17:27.687 line:80%
What's up, Mr. Groom?

1779
01:17:27.895 --> 01:17:29.479 line:80%
- Where are you off to, huh?
- Oh!

1780
01:17:30.395 --> 01:17:32.145 line:80%
Sorry about yesterday.

1781
01:17:33.062 --> 01:17:34.854 line:80%
I got mad at you.

1782
01:17:35.562 --> 01:17:36.937 line:80%
I'm heading out now.

1783
01:17:38.145 --> 01:17:39.354 line:80%
Ugh.

1784
01:17:41.270 --> 01:17:42.729 line:80%
If I've hurt you in any way,
please forgive me.

1785
01:17:43.437 --> 01:17:45.229 line:80%
I end up stepping on you every day.

1786
01:17:47.104 --> 01:17:48.395 line:80%
Mahadev!

1787
01:17:51.145 --> 01:17:56.187 line:80%
I'm lucky to have both of you in my life.

1788
01:17:57.104 --> 01:17:58.520 line:80%
- Really?
- What's wrong?

1789
01:17:59.479 --> 01:18:00.812 line:80%
You in some kind of trouble?

1790
01:18:00.895 --> 01:18:02.604 line:80%
No, no, no.

1791
01:18:04.187 --> 01:18:06.312 line:80%
I just want to say something
to both of you.

1792
01:18:08.104 --> 01:18:11.895 line:80%
If I've hurt you in any way,
knowingly or unknowingly,

1793
01:18:11.979 --> 01:18:13.520 line:80%
if I've made any mistakes,

1794
01:18:14.312 --> 01:18:15.979 line:80%
please forgive me.

1795
01:18:16.145 --> 01:18:17.812 line:80%
What are you saying, Brother?

1796
01:18:18.520 --> 01:18:21.104 line:80%
- Yes! We'd die for you.
- Yeah.

1797
01:18:21.229 --> 01:18:23.395 line:80%
I don't know why, but I feel like

1798
01:18:23.479 --> 01:18:25.145 line:80%
I've hurt your feelings.

1799
01:18:25.395 --> 01:18:26.604 line:80%
Yeah, you have.

1800
01:18:26.770 --> 01:18:27.854 line:80%
What are you saying, Brother?

1801
01:18:27.937 --> 01:18:29.395 line:80%
You're my ideal.

1802
01:18:29.520 --> 01:18:30.687 line:80%
I haven't hurt your feelings?

1803
01:18:31.229 --> 01:18:32.187 line:80%
Damn.

1804
01:18:33.770 --> 01:18:35.020 line:80%
Then whose curse is at work here?

1805
01:18:35.104 --> 01:18:36.020 line:80%
Curse?

1806
01:18:36.812 --> 01:18:38.770 line:80%
Yeah, it...

1807
01:18:39.187 --> 01:18:40.479 line:80%
I'll tell you later.

1808
01:18:41.437 --> 01:18:45.729 line:80%
First, think about whose feelings
I might've hurt in Banaras.

1809
01:18:47.187 --> 01:18:51.895 line:80%
There's only one guy in Banaras
whose feelings you've hurt badly.

1810
01:18:52.604 --> 01:18:53.479 line:80%
Who?

1811
01:18:59.562 --> 01:19:00.645 line:80%
So, Dad,

1812
01:19:01.020 --> 01:19:02.479 line:80%
here's my problem.

1813
01:19:02.937 --> 01:19:04.937 line:80%
God only knows
whose curse is at work here.

1814
01:19:05.437 --> 01:19:06.854 line:80%
I'm stuck on the 29th!

1815
01:19:06.937 --> 01:19:08.395 line:80%
The day never changes to the 30th for me.

1816
01:19:08.479 --> 01:19:09.229 line:80%
Huh?

1817
01:19:09.395 --> 01:19:11.395 line:80%
The 30th, the date won't change for me.

1818
01:19:11.979 --> 01:19:13.354 line:80%
- What's he saying?
- There you go.

1819
01:19:14.104 --> 01:19:15.604 line:80%
You were so excited that day.

1820
01:19:15.687 --> 01:19:17.312 line:80%
"30th is perfect, just perfect!"

1821
01:19:17.395 --> 01:19:18.812 line:80%
Now the date won't change to 30th for him.

1822
01:19:18.895 --> 01:19:19.145 line:80%
Yes.

1823
01:19:19.229 --> 01:19:21.895 line:80%
The offer I got from the electricity
department was better.

1824
01:19:21.979 --> 01:19:23.145 line:80%
At least the day would've
changed to the 30th.

1825
01:19:23.229 --> 01:19:24.187 line:80%
Right.

1826
01:19:24.520 --> 01:19:27.895 line:80%
Nephew, do you want me to hurt your
brother-in-law's feelings right here?

1827
01:19:28.062 --> 01:19:29.645 line:80%
He's talking too much.

1828
01:19:32.937 --> 01:19:34.187 line:80%
Hey... Son...

1829
01:19:34.479 --> 01:19:36.145 line:80%
I'm your wife's brother-in-law.

1830
01:19:37.437 --> 01:19:38.645 line:80%
If I've hurt you in any way,
please forgive me.

1831
01:19:38.729 --> 01:19:40.354 line:80%
Who touches his feet, huh?

1832
01:19:41.270 --> 01:19:43.145 line:80%
Dad, please tell me, what should I do?

1833
01:19:43.229 --> 01:19:44.354 line:80%
What should I really do?

1834
01:19:44.437 --> 01:19:46.104 line:80%
What should I say?

1835
01:19:46.854 --> 01:19:48.229 line:80%
Have you told your dad?

1836
01:19:48.395 --> 01:19:49.270 line:80%
What?

1837
01:19:49.354 --> 01:19:50.645 line:80%
About this illness?

1838
01:19:51.562 --> 01:19:52.895 line:80%
I have.

1839
01:19:52.979 --> 01:19:54.229 line:80%
I've told everyone,

1840
01:19:54.687 --> 01:19:56.479 line:80%
but no one believes me.

1841
01:19:58.895 --> 01:20:00.145 line:80%
So, Dad, the thing is,

1842
01:20:00.770 --> 01:20:01.979 line:80%
if tomorrow the date changes to the 30th,

1843
01:20:02.229 --> 01:20:03.562 line:80%
I'll be here with the wedding procession.

1844
01:20:04.770 --> 01:20:06.437 line:80%
If it doesn't, then...

1845
01:20:06.604 --> 01:20:07.604 line:80%
Then?

1846
01:20:11.479 --> 01:20:12.645 line:80%
What did he say?

1847
01:20:39.937 --> 01:20:41.229 line:80%
Brother Ranjan!

1848
01:20:41.354 --> 01:20:42.520 line:80%
Hey, where are you off to?

1849
01:20:42.604 --> 01:20:43.854 line:80%
Hey, listen for a second.

1850
01:20:43.937 --> 01:20:45.062 line:80%
- Where are you headed?
- Look...

1851
01:20:45.145 --> 01:20:46.520 line:80%
You should at least put
on some turmeric first.

1852
01:20:48.520 --> 01:20:49.854 line:80%
Give me a quarter.

1853
01:21:16.062 --> 01:21:17.895 line:80%
I'm sorry, Titli.

1854
01:21:19.312 --> 01:21:22.520 line:80%
Your "Babu" never did anything for you.

1855
01:21:25.979 --> 01:21:27.562 line:80%
Nor for himself, either.

1856
01:21:29.604 --> 01:21:31.937 line:80%
I don't have any other choice now.

1857
01:21:36.687 --> 01:21:38.687 line:80%
It's way too high, way too high.

1858
01:21:40.395 --> 01:21:42.520 line:80%
I'm not going to mess up your 30th

1859
01:21:43.145 --> 01:21:45.812 line:80%
just because of my bad luck with the 29th.

1860
01:21:45.979 --> 01:21:47.395 line:80%
I won't!

1861
01:21:49.937 --> 01:21:51.270 line:80%
Oh, Holy Ganges,

1862
01:21:53.437 --> 01:21:54.979 line:80%
please ensure my salvation.

1863
01:22:01.687 --> 01:22:02.562 line:80%
What's up?

1864
01:22:02.937 --> 01:22:03.854 line:80%
Who are you?

1865
01:22:05.104 --> 01:22:07.229 line:80%
You don't think this
is a risky spot for a selfie?

1866
01:22:08.020 --> 01:22:09.229 line:80%
You'll fall, get down.

1867
01:22:10.770 --> 01:22:11.729 line:80%
Get down now.

1868
01:22:16.479 --> 01:22:18.687 line:80%
Hey, I meant get down on the road,
not into the river.

1869
01:22:19.895 --> 01:22:22.395 line:80%
They don't even let you
commit suicide in peace.

1870
01:22:26.854 --> 01:22:28.979 line:80%
Are you swimming or drowning?

1871
01:22:31.604 --> 01:22:32.687 line:80%
Mahadev...

1872
01:22:46.895 --> 01:22:48.104 line:80%
Come on, seriously...

1873
01:22:49.979 --> 01:22:51.604 line:80%
Just stick two fingers
in your mouth like this,

1874
01:22:51.687 --> 01:22:52.812 line:80%
and all the water will come out.

1875
01:22:52.895 --> 01:22:53.895 line:80%
That's what I did.

1876
01:22:53.979 --> 01:22:54.937 line:80%
I'm fine.

1877
01:22:55.020 --> 01:22:56.729 line:80%
Totally killed my buzz too!

1878
01:22:58.270 --> 01:22:59.312 line:80%
Are you good?

1879
01:23:03.354 --> 01:23:04.520 line:80%
Why were you thinking
about ending your life?

1880
01:23:07.979 --> 01:23:09.270 line:80%
What was I supposed to do?

1881
01:23:09.895 --> 01:23:11.812 line:80%
I had no other choice.

1882
01:23:13.854 --> 01:23:15.104 line:80%
I get it.

1883
01:23:16.270 --> 01:23:20.854 line:80%
Sometimes, you're in a situation
you just can't explain to anyone.

1884
01:23:23.729 --> 01:23:24.645 line:80%
Here you go.

1885
01:23:25.770 --> 01:23:26.687 line:80%
What's your name?

1886
01:23:30.562 --> 01:23:31.770 line:80%
Hamid Ansari.

1887
01:23:32.812 --> 01:23:33.937 line:80%
You're from Monal?

1888
01:23:35.479 --> 01:23:36.687 line:80%
I'm originally from Loharia,

1889
01:23:37.062 --> 01:23:39.437 line:80%
but I've been here
for the last seven years.

1890
01:23:40.979 --> 01:23:42.104 line:80%
Your family?

1891
01:23:43.895 --> 01:23:46.437 line:80%
They're back home in the village.

1892
01:23:48.104 --> 01:23:50.520 line:80%
Have you imagined what would have
happened to them if you had died?

1893
01:23:53.770 --> 01:23:56.104 line:80%
Why were you ending your life?
What's the problem?

1894
01:23:58.020 --> 01:24:00.562 line:80%
The same thing half
of our population is dealing with.

1895
01:24:01.229 --> 01:24:04.020 line:80%
I see, you're heartbroken.

1896
01:24:05.354 --> 01:24:06.312 line:80%
No.

1897
01:24:06.729 --> 01:24:08.104 line:80%
It's the government job thing.

1898
01:24:09.020 --> 01:24:11.979 line:80%
Damn, this government job issue...

1899
01:24:13.187 --> 01:24:14.354 line:80%
I get it.

1900
01:24:20.979 --> 01:24:21.729 line:80%
Hey,

1901
01:24:23.020 --> 01:24:23.895 line:80%
tell me something

1902
01:24:24.729 --> 01:24:26.729 line:80%
if you get a job,
you won't end your life, right?

1903
01:24:26.979 --> 01:24:29.187 line:80%
Why would I die if I get a job, Brother?

1904
01:24:30.770 --> 01:24:32.437 line:80%
Perfect!

1905
01:24:33.145 --> 01:24:35.812 line:80%
You're my selfish good deed!

1906
01:24:37.145 --> 01:24:40.020 line:80%
Now, Ranjan Tiwari will risk
his own life to get you that job.

1907
01:24:40.270 --> 01:24:41.312 line:80%
Just wait and watch.

1908
01:24:41.812 --> 01:24:44.020 line:80%
From now on,
Ansari and Tiwari are brothers.

1909
01:24:45.270 --> 01:24:46.354 line:80%
Peon!

1910
01:24:46.812 --> 01:24:48.187 line:80%
Two teas, please.

1911
01:24:50.020 --> 01:24:51.854 line:80%
Here to pay your dues?

1912
01:24:53.270 --> 01:24:56.020 line:80%
Guru-ji,
I'll get you the money in a few days.

1913
01:24:57.604 --> 01:24:59.520 line:80%
Peon, forget the tea!

1914
01:24:59.604 --> 01:25:00.520 line:80%
Hey...

1915
01:25:00.604 --> 01:25:02.312 line:80%
No rush, take your time.

1916
01:25:02.395 --> 01:25:04.729 line:80%
Did he mention he's getting a big dowry?

1917
01:25:04.812 --> 01:25:07.395 line:80%
My bride's my dowry.
I don't go in for that stuff.

1918
01:25:07.479 --> 01:25:09.354 line:80%
So, what's up? Why are you here?

1919
01:25:09.479 --> 01:25:11.854 line:80%
Guru-ji, this is my friend, Hamid.

1920
01:25:11.937 --> 01:25:12.937 line:80%
Hello.

1921
01:25:13.020 --> 01:25:15.104 line:80%
I wanted to talk to you about his job.

1922
01:25:15.312 --> 01:25:16.562 line:80%
Yeah, he'll get it.

1923
01:25:16.854 --> 01:25:19.520 line:80%
Tell him about the payment details.

1924
01:25:19.729 --> 01:25:22.729 line:80%
Well, Guru-ji,
he's a little short on cash.

1925
01:25:22.937 --> 01:25:24.854 line:80%
I'll take care of it.
Guru-ji, I'll figure something out.

1926
01:25:24.937 --> 01:25:27.395 line:80%
No, I don't want to pay for a job.

1927
01:25:27.479 --> 01:25:29.604 line:80%
You're not willing to pay for a job?

1928
01:25:29.687 --> 01:25:31.812 line:80%
I'm not here for charity.

1929
01:25:32.312 --> 01:25:34.020 line:80%
It's a risky job, ask him.

1930
01:25:34.104 --> 01:25:35.770 line:80%
- No, you're right.
- Obviously, I'm right.

1931
01:25:35.854 --> 01:25:39.437 line:80%
You'll get the job
and enjoy the perks of life.

1932
01:25:39.520 --> 01:25:42.020 line:80%
After you're gone,
your wife will be set with your benefits.

1933
01:25:42.104 --> 01:25:43.145 line:80%
What do I get out of this?

1934
01:25:43.229 --> 01:25:44.229 line:80%
Nothing?

1935
01:25:44.312 --> 01:25:46.437 line:80%
Tell him, man.
You'll need to pay for it.

1936
01:25:46.562 --> 01:25:47.687 line:80%
We'll sort it out, we'll sort it.

1937
01:25:47.770 --> 01:25:49.437 line:80%
Let me make this clear.

1938
01:25:49.895 --> 01:25:51.520 line:80%
First off, I don't have the money.

1939
01:25:51.604 --> 01:25:53.437 line:80%
Plus, I don't want to pay to get a job.

1940
01:25:53.854 --> 01:25:55.604 line:80%
Oh my God!

1941
01:25:55.895 --> 01:25:58.437 line:80%
Where did you find this freedom fighter?

1942
01:25:58.604 --> 01:26:00.187 line:80%
What's your name, Brother?

1943
01:26:00.854 --> 01:26:02.854 line:80%
Hamid... Hamid Ansari.

1944
01:26:03.895 --> 01:26:05.187 line:80%
How old are you?

1945
01:26:06.020 --> 01:26:06.729 line:80%
26.

1946
01:26:06.812 --> 01:26:10.687 line:80%
Struggle for another year or two,
and we'll get it done.

1947
01:26:10.770 --> 01:26:14.020 line:80%
We'll team up and make it happen.
Now leave him be, alright?

1948
01:26:14.270 --> 01:26:15.479 line:80%
Go wait outside.

1949
01:26:16.979 --> 01:26:18.729 line:80%
You stay here.

1950
01:26:19.562 --> 01:26:20.354 line:80%
Sit down, man.

1951
01:26:20.437 --> 01:26:21.437 line:80%
You can go,

1952
01:26:22.145 --> 01:26:23.145 line:80%
he'll join you soon.

1953
01:26:23.229 --> 01:26:24.020 line:80%
I'll be right with you.

1954
01:26:25.145 --> 01:26:26.729 line:80%
Where did you find this guy?

1955
01:26:27.729 --> 01:26:29.270 line:80%
What do I say, Guru-ji...

1956
01:26:32.229 --> 01:26:33.562 line:80%
He's a good guy, Guru-ji.

1957
01:26:34.104 --> 01:26:35.145 line:80%
Please, help him out.

1958
01:26:35.229 --> 01:26:37.354 line:80%
"He's a good guy, please help him out!"

1959
01:26:38.729 --> 01:26:39.770 line:80%
There's only one way to fix this.

1960
01:26:39.854 --> 01:26:40.854 line:80%
What's that?

1961
01:26:41.145 --> 01:26:44.562 line:80%
You give up your job,
and he'll take your spot.

1962
01:26:46.020 --> 01:26:47.145 line:80%
What's that supposed to mean?

1963
01:26:47.312 --> 01:26:50.270 line:80%
He's the 15th guy

1964
01:26:51.312 --> 01:26:53.729 line:80%
I took off the list and swapped with you!

1965
01:26:54.604 --> 01:26:56.229 line:80%
Hamid Ansari.

1966
01:26:57.520 --> 01:27:00.645 line:80%
You'll lose your job,
and I'll lose my business.

1967
01:27:01.145 --> 01:27:03.187 line:80%
What's wrong with this generation,
seriously?!

1968
01:27:09.187 --> 01:27:11.479 line:80%
- Sister...!
- So you're saying

1969
01:27:11.729 --> 01:27:13.354 line:80%
he dies and comes back
to life every single day?

1970
01:27:13.437 --> 01:27:14.604 line:80%
Yep, every day!

1971
01:27:14.770 --> 01:27:15.854 line:80%
Every single day!

1972
01:27:15.979 --> 01:27:18.437 line:80%
I left my henna ceremony just
to hear this crap?

1973
01:27:18.520 --> 01:27:19.687 line:80%
It's just henna, chill out.

1974
01:27:19.812 --> 01:27:22.020 line:80%
It's not like you walked out
in the middle of taking a dump!

1975
01:27:22.104 --> 01:27:23.270 line:80%
Ugh, that's gross!

1976
01:27:23.354 --> 01:27:24.895 line:80%
You can just redo it.
You're doing it every day anyway.

1977
01:27:24.979 --> 01:27:26.687 line:80%
Come on, Brother,
why are you yelling at your sister-in-law?

1978
01:27:26.770 --> 01:27:29.562 line:80%
I dare him to yell at me.
I'll pull his tongue out!

1979
01:27:29.812 --> 01:27:32.354 line:80%
And you... you're not even my husband yet!

1980
01:27:32.437 --> 01:27:34.354 line:80%
Don't give me that husband attitude.

1981
01:27:34.520 --> 01:27:35.770 line:80%
- I'm showing attitude?
- Yup, you are!

1982
01:27:35.854 --> 01:27:38.020 line:80%
What about you?
Always complaining about the henna?

1983
01:27:38.104 --> 01:27:40.020 line:80%
Alright, alright, stop fighting already.

1984
01:27:40.645 --> 01:27:41.895 line:80%
Tell me,

1985
01:27:42.687 --> 01:27:44.270 line:80%
why are you even getting into this?

1986
01:27:44.354 --> 01:27:46.187 line:80%
You worked hard to get that job.

1987
01:27:46.520 --> 01:27:49.937 line:80%
Uncle, Hamid actually deserves this job.

1988
01:27:50.020 --> 01:27:52.312 line:80%
- Come on, man.
- I don't know who Hamid is.

1989
01:27:52.437 --> 01:27:54.645 line:80%
If it was meant for him,
he would've gotten it.

1990
01:27:54.729 --> 01:27:57.104 line:80%
- Yeah.
- It was meant for you, so you got it.

1991
01:27:57.479 --> 01:27:59.229 line:80%
If Hamid doesn't get the job,

1992
01:27:59.854 --> 01:28:01.020 line:80%
he's going to die.

1993
01:28:01.270 --> 01:28:02.437 line:80%
Again.

1994
01:28:03.229 --> 01:28:04.937 line:80%
Don't make me whack you!

1995
01:28:05.020 --> 01:28:07.729 line:80%
Whether he dies or not,
you're definitely die by my hands today.

1996
01:28:07.812 --> 01:28:09.312 line:80%
I'm right here,
go ahead and do it. Kill me.

1997
01:28:09.395 --> 01:28:10.645 line:80%
- Kill me again.
- You guys are fighting again?

1998
01:28:10.729 --> 01:28:12.062 line:80%
- Should I?
- Chill out.

1999
01:28:12.354 --> 01:28:15.145 line:80%
Listen, if you don't get that job,
you won't be able to get married either.

2000
01:28:15.562 --> 01:28:16.854 line:80%
And if you can't get married,

2001
01:28:16.937 --> 01:28:18.729 line:80%
you'll probably end up taking your life.

2002
01:28:19.020 --> 01:28:20.479 line:80%
And if you do that,

2003
01:28:20.687 --> 01:28:22.770 line:80%
I'll go find Hamid and kill him.

2004
01:28:23.020 --> 01:28:23.979 line:80%
Yeah, Brother.

2005
01:28:24.270 --> 01:28:25.979 line:80%
If he's going to die anyway,

2006
01:28:26.395 --> 01:28:27.895 line:80%
why even bother saving him?

2007
01:28:27.979 --> 01:28:30.020 line:80%
Uncle, it's important that we save Hamid.

2008
01:28:30.729 --> 01:28:32.729 line:80%
I think saving him is the good deed
I am supposed to do.

2009
01:28:33.020 --> 01:28:35.020 line:80%
and it's why all this mess started
in the first place.

2010
01:28:35.854 --> 01:28:36.645 line:80%
Hold up.

2011
01:28:36.979 --> 01:28:40.562 line:80%
You made a promise
at Lord Shiva's temple, right?

2012
01:28:40.812 --> 01:28:41.687 line:80%
Yeah.

2013
01:28:43.187 --> 01:28:44.479 line:80%
Then it's no big deal!

2014
01:28:45.020 --> 01:28:45.979 line:80%
What?

2015
01:28:46.062 --> 01:28:48.187 line:80%
Well, Hamid's Muslim.

2016
01:28:48.562 --> 01:28:49.937 line:80%
- Huh?
- Hmm.

2017
01:28:54.270 --> 01:28:55.729 line:80%
How do you even do this?

2018
01:28:56.812 --> 01:28:58.854 line:80%
Listen, buddy, come with me,

2019
01:28:59.145 --> 01:29:02.687 line:80%
I've got a surprise
bachelor's party lined up for you.

2020
01:29:02.770 --> 01:29:03.812 line:80%
- Uncle...
- Forget the surprise party.

2021
01:29:03.895 --> 01:29:05.145 line:80%
Just hear me out.
Take me with you.

2022
01:29:05.229 --> 01:29:06.479 line:80%
- What? What bachelor party?
- Brother?

2023
01:29:06.562 --> 01:29:07.562 line:80%
- Where are you going?
- Brother?

2024
01:29:07.645 --> 01:29:09.145 line:80%
- Babu!
-
God!

2025
01:29:10.270 --> 01:29:11.437 line:80%
You're such a weirdo.

2026
01:29:11.520 --> 01:29:12.937 line:80%
You're trying to change his fate

2027
01:29:13.020 --> 01:29:14.729 line:80%
hen he's just going
to die again tomorrow anyway.

2028
01:29:14.812 --> 01:29:15.604 line:80%
God!

2029
01:29:15.687 --> 01:29:17.895 line:80%
You're going to get scolded,
and I'm going to get scolded by Dad too.

2030
01:29:17.979 --> 01:29:19.687 line:80%
Sister, please, just drive faster.

2031
01:29:19.854 --> 01:29:20.895 line:80%
What do you want me to do, make it fly?

2032
01:29:20.979 --> 01:29:22.270 line:80%
Yes, Sister, make it fly.

2033
01:29:22.354 --> 01:29:23.604 line:80%
Hamid, no!

2034
01:29:23.812 --> 01:29:26.854 line:80%
Hamid, stop!

2035
01:29:26.937 --> 01:29:28.395 line:80%
- Go, go, go!
- Hold on, hold on, hold on.

2036
01:29:28.479 --> 01:29:30.979 line:80%
You see your life slipping away,

2037
